Seafood Boil Ramen 🍜

This is a super quick seafood boil ramen noodles you can make in 15min! All you need is ramen, sausage, shrimp, egg, & your fav spices. It’s perfect for spicy lunch or a light dinner! Hope you all enjoy 😋💙

Cajun Shrimp Creole 🦐

This is one of my most favorite dishes EVER!! Whenever I’m back home in Florida or in NOLA I always have to order some. It’s spicy and hearty! I make mine with some Stella Rosa which balances out the spiciness. Pairs perfect with white rice. I hope you all enjoy this delicious southern creole meal 😋💙

I took a self love trip to Jamaica 🇯🇲🌴

I had such a great time at the Zoëtry Montego Bay resort! My butlers Kyle & Michael took great care of me and made sure my stay with super relaxing. 🧘🏽‍♀️The spa was amazing & I had the best massage. It’s a all inclusive resort, but the food/drinks was AMAZING!!! It was super lowkey and a gated resort, so it’s perfect for a solo trip or a romantic getaway. I truly enjoyed myself on this trip!! I feel recharged and ready to get back to everyday life! I HIGHLY recommend this resort and just traveling to relax in general! Self love is the best love 🇯🇲🫶🏽 I can’t wait to come back to Jamaica!
Cheers to tan lines & not giving a F*k 💚🇯🇲 @missdaphneerenae

Lamb Shank Dinner 🍗

I’m FINALLY back with a new recipe! I decided to make this yummy lamb shank with black eyed peas and white rice. The lamb shank had the perfect balance of sweetness, savory, & spice! Make sure you really marinate it overnight and bake on 450 degrees. It was so juicy and tender, it fell right off the bone! Try this for your next Sunday dinner 😋 ENJOY! 💙
